NAME
    String::Urandom - Generate a truely random string

SYNOPSIS
      use String::Urandom;

      my $obj = new String::Urandom;

      # set the string length 
      $obj->str_length(255);

      # set the characters
      $obj->str_chars('a b c 1 2 3');

      # print the result
      print $obj->rand_string, "\n";

DESCRIPTION
    Using output from /dev/urandom. Simply convert bytes into 8-bit
    characters.

METHODS
  str_length
    This function will set/get the string character length.

    The default value is: 32

      $obj->str_length(255);

  str_chars
    This function will set/get characters used when generating a string.

    The default value is: a-z A-Z 0-9

      $obj->str_chars('a e i o u 1 2 3');

  rand_string
    This function will generate a random string.

      $obj->rand_string;

REQUIREMENTS
    Any flavour of UNIX that supports /dev/urandom

SEE ALSO
    urandom(4)

AUTHOR
    Marc S. Brooks <mbrooks@cpan.org> <http://mbrooks.info>

